unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Ferrothorn
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It fights by shooting its three spiky feelers. It can stick to the ceiling of a cave.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Klink
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: Two bodies comprise a single Pokémon. It generates energy by spinning.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Klang
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is a master of teamwork. It can generate enough electricity to power a small town.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Klinklang
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: The red core functions as an energy tank. It can launch gears with astounding speed.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Tynamo
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: These Pokémon move in schools. They can generate a charge equal to a lightning bolt.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Eelektrik
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It wraps its long body around prey, then shocks them with electricity from its circular patches.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Evolves into Eelektross with a Thunder Stone.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Eelektross
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It latches onto prey with its sucker mouth, then drags the prey into the ocean.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Elgyem
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: This Pokémon was discovered 50 years ago in a desert. It uses its psychic power to squeeze its foe's brain.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Beheeyem
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It can manipulate an opponent's memory. It is said to have come from outer space.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Litwick
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It shines a light that absorbs the life force of people and Pokémon. It leads them to the Ghost World.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Lampent
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It arrives near the moment of death and steals the spirit from the body.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Evolves into Chandelure with a Dusk Stone.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Chandelure
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Axew
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Fraxure
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: After a territorial dispute, it sharpens its dull tusks on river rocks.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Haxorus
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It can cut through steel. It is a kind Pokémon, but it is terrifying when angered.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Cubchoo
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back up because the mucus is the raw material for its moves.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Beartic
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It can make its breath freeze at will. It creates pathways across the ocean waters by freezing them.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Cryogonal
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is born in snow clouds. It uses its chains of ice to capture prey.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Shelmet
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: When attacked, it closes the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Evolves into Accelgor when traded for a Karrablast.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Accelgor
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It moves with the speed of a ninja. It battles by spitting a liquid that is both poisonous and sticky.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Stunfisk
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. It patiently waits for prey to blunder into its range.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Mienfoo
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It has a flurry of kicks and chops. It is said that its fighting style is like a dance.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Mienshao
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It uses the fur on its arms as a whip. Its arm attacks are like a flash of lightning.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Druddigon
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It runs through the narrow tunnels of caves, scraping its body against the walls to sharpen its scales.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Golett
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is said that they were created by an ancient civilization. They have been active for thousands of years.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Golurk
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Pawniard
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It follows the orders of a Bisharp. It is a loyal and devoted Pokémon.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Bisharp
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is the leader of a pack of Pawniard. It will not tolerate failure from its minions.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Bouffalant
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It can knock a train off the tracks with its headbutts. It is a very violent Pokémon.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Rufflet
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It has a very aggressive nature. It will pick a fight with any Pokémon, no matter how much bigger it is.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Braviary
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is known as the 'hero of the skies.' It will fight for its friends, even if it is injured.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Vullaby
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It protects its rear with a bone. It can't fly very well yet, so it hops around.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Mandibuzz
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It makes a nest out of bones. It is a clumsy flier.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Heatmor
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It breathes through a hole in its tail. It is a natural predator of Durant.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Durant
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Deino
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It has the habit of biting anything that moves. It can't see, so it relies on its other senses.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Zweilous
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: The two heads do not get along. They are always fighting over food.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Hydreigon
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It responds to movement by attacking. This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Larvesta
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It is said that it was born from the sun. It can spew fire from its five horns to repel foes.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Volcarona
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: When volcanic ash darkens the atmosphere, it is said that it appears and replaces the sun.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Cobalion
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It has a body and heart of steel. It fought with its comrades to protect Pokémon.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Terrakion
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in a single blow.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Virizion
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It fought with its comrades to protect Pokémon. It is said that its horns are like blades.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Tornadus
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Therian Forme with a Reveal Glass.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Thundurus
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Therian Forme with a Reveal Glass.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Reshiram
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Zekrom
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Landorus
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: The energy that comes from its tail builds nutrition in the soil, making the land fertile.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Therian Forme with a Reveal Glass.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Kyurem
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It can produce ultracold air. Its body is frozen.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Legendary. Can fuse with Reshiram or Zekrom.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Keldeo
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Mythical. Can change to Resolute Form after learning Secret Sword.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Meloetta
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
unova_pokedex_part_3.evolution: Mythical. Can change to Pirouette Forme by using Relic Song.

unova_pokedex_part_3.name: Genesect
unova_pokedex_part_3.description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
